unmodifiableNavigableMap

public static <K,V> NavigableMap<K,V> unmodifiableNavigableMap(NavigableMap<? extends K,? extends V> navigableMap)
Returns an unmodifiable view of the specified NavigableMap. Attempts to modify the returned map directly, via its collection views, or via its subSet, headSet, or tailSet views, will result in UnsupportedOperationExceptions.

The returned map will be serializable if the specified navigable map is serializable.

Parameters:
navigableMap - the given navigable map
Returns:
an unmodifiable view of the given navigable map

synchronizedNavigableMap

public static <K,V> NavigableMap<K,V> synchronizedNavigableMap(NavigableMap<K,V> navigableMap)
Returns a synchronized (thread-safe) NavigableMap backed by the specified navigable map. In order to guarantee serial access, it is critical that all access to the backing map is accomplished through the returned map (or its views).

Clients must manually synchronize on the returned navigable map when iterating over any of its collection views, or the collections views of any of its subMap, headMap or tailMap views.

The returned map will be serializable if the specified navigable map is serializable.

Parameters:
navigableMap - the specified map to synchronize
Returns:
a synchronized view of the specified NavigableMap

synchronizedBoundedMap

public static <K,V> BoundedMap<K,V> synchronizedBoundedMap(BoundedMap<K,V> boundedMap)
Returns a synchronized (thread-safe) BoundedMap backed by the specified bounded map. In order to guarantee serial access, it is critical that all access to the backing map is accomplished through the returned map (or its views).

Clients must manually synchronize on the returned map when iterating over any of its collection views.

The returned bounded map will be serializable if the specified bounded map is serializable.

Parameters:
boundedMap - the specified bounded map to synchronize
Returns:
a synchronized view of the specified BoundedMap
